  "instructions": [
    "Preheat tandoor oven to 200°C (400°F) with clay bricks for even heat distribution.",
    "In a small bowl, mix bicarbonate of soda, smoked paprika, garlic powder, and olive oil for the crust blend.",
    "Place duck breasts skin-side down on the tandoor oven rack, ensuring even contact with the heat source.",
    "Brush duck skin with the crust blend and roast for 10-12 minutes until skin is crisp and meat is tender."
